DIGEST
SB 196 Original 2026 Regular Session Foil
Present law requires that a taxpayer do one of the following upon receipt of a notice of
assessment and right to appeal for local sales and use taxes:
(1) Pay the amount of the assessment within sixty calendar days from the date of the
notice.
(2) Appeal to the Board of Tax Appeals, hereinafter "BTA", for redetermination of the
assessment within sixty calendar days from the date of the notice.
(3) Pay under protest within sixty calendar days from the date of the notice, and then
either file suit or file a petition with the BTA.
(4) Agree in writing with the collector to a mediation within fifteen calendar days from
